message: I know that my edit needs consensus before being executed but the problem is that that consensus will never be reached.  Not even voting is allowed in discussion forums.
Please see the discussion forum before you revert this edit.
I know what you are saying, but see my comment on the discussion page before you go back to the old revision.
You idiots!  You are ruining what is supposed to be the best night of my life!  And all of this over some idiotic encyclopedia!

How about this: I get to have this on here for the next five minutes and only the next five minutes.  Then each of you can post something here too.  It is only fair.  I've been planning this for ages.
What is wrong with what I am doing?  THIS IS NOT A PROFESSIONAL ENCYCLOPEDIA!
Come on, that's no fair!  I only got a few seconds, don't do it again.  Why can't I?  I'm about to call my fiancee right now.
Please let me keep this up for 10 minutes, thank you
I'm just playing around.  I'll change it back and I do agree with the current consensus.
NO!  No consensus has been reached.
fine, then I will have to make the sentence uncontroversial
Fine!  Then we will have to settle with this just to let readers know that not everything in here is unbiased.
No, this is the agreed upon consensus.
This also needs to be omitted for neutrality standards.
For a discussion of this sentence, please see my comment and respond before you make any changes or revisions.
/* Statistics */Date maintenance tags and general  fixes
/* United States */ last source was very unreliable
/* Controversial views */ social conservatives in some societies approve of polygamy
I explained who the first lesbian couple to get married in England were.
/* United States */ this will be hypocritical since I am not a Barna supporter particularly. I think he is right here. And they do process statistics in a scholarly manner
/* Definitions */ removing requested citation (statement was self-verifying); lowercasing.
returning to status quo while discussion continues
